ic and unrelenting, this counterterror state prioritizes speculative practices over facts, and ignores everyday forms of violence across climate, capital, and health in an unprecedented effort to anticipate and eliminate terror threats-real, imagined, and emergent.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aNational securityzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aNational securityzUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aTerrorismzUnited StatesxPreventionxHistoryy20th century. 0aTerrorismzUnited StatesxPreventionxHistoryy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071182040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822375999zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822375999423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822375999.jpg  a978-3-11-071182-0  DUK eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles